From 54bf2dc2c7b9a75c29425d2636c6aa7607259fe8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 11:02:49 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Diff view: re-enable LSP via createModelReference + full
 inner-editor contributions
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 8.6's LSP path was working pre-rollback, but the re-landed series
(patches 0036-0037) lost two pieces. This patch restores both.

1) Inner-editor contributions filter dropped. Phase 9.5 (0058) allow-
listed only `editor.contrib.review` so the native comment controller
attaches. That filter also stripped hover, goto-definition, peek, find-
references, etc. — none of which are individually obvious because they
register themselves into the global list and only instantiate when the
field is left undefined. Pass `{}` for both inner editor option blocks
so the diff editor picks up the full registered-contribution set, same
as a regular file editor. Comments still attach because
`editor.contrib.review` is part of the default set.

2) file:// upgrade for the head model. The previous code only used the
file:// URI when `IModelService.getModel(headFileUri)` returned an
existing model — i.e. only when the user had already opened the file in
another editor. Typical flow (open PR, working tree on PR head, file
not previously opened) hit the virtual `krt-pr-head://` URI instead, and
language extensions don't activate against KRT-internal schemes.

Restored the original async-resolution path: render synchronously with
virtual models for instant visibility, then asynchronously call
`ITextModelService.createModelReference(file://...)` once `getHeadSha`
confirms the working tree is on the PR head SHA. The reference goes
through the workbench's normal file-loading path, which triggers
language-extension activation. Base side upgrades to `krt-git://` via
the existing content provider so both sides become full-content; flip
`hideUnchangedRegions` on so the visual stays focused on the changed
regions plus a few lines of real surrounding context. realLines becomes
identity for full-content sides; line-numbers fall back to Monaco's
built-in numbering. Comment-resource registry re-registers at the new
URIs so `KrtPrCommentController` sees the right set.

Plus: register passthrough providers for `krt-pr-base://` and
`krt-pr-head://` schemes in `KrtGitContentProviderContribution` so
downstream `createModelReference` calls (peek, hover, language services)
don't error with "Unable to resolve resource" on the virtual URIs.

When the working tree isn't on the PR head, the upgrade logs "(no LSP).
Check out the PR head SHA to enable LSP." and stays on virtuals.

